3.00	Footcandles	Foot-candle	A foot-candle (sometimes foot candle; abbreviated fc, lm/ftÂ², or sometimes ft-c) is a non-SI unit of illuminance or light intensity widely used in photography, film, television, conservation lighting, and the lighting industry. The name "footcandle" conveys "the illuminance cast on a surface by a one-candela source one foot away."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a3/Foot_candle.jpg/150px-Foot_candle.jpg
